Text.Value: I will honour Shadowheart's memory, for the rest of my days.
*So choose well, choose wisely - to your own nature be true.*
I will submit myself for study to the Society of Brilliance. More research into illithids and Bhaal's blood will make the world safer.
I will honour Gale's memory as best I can, for the rest of my days.
*Isobel, the Cleric of Selûne. Her death weighs upon you still.*
*You still do not know the full extent of the scars that you left, but you will heal them, one by one.*
*Karlach. Her death weighs upon you still.*
*You will never be able to undo all the death you once wrought in his name.*

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC HAS PARTNER BUT MISSED EVERYONE ELSE

Text.Value: I will honour Astarion's memory, for the rest of my days.
*Father Bhaal loves no death more than that of his own children. He will welcome the challenge.*
I can still aid the Gate from the Undercity. Organise supply chains, raise gold for the hospitals.
*Alfira, the Bard of the Emerald Grove. Her death weighs upon you still.*
*Of all those you killed in your Father's name, one lingers in your mind even now.*
*Your family will be what you make of it, who you love, who you choose.*
*A rush of pleasure wells up within you at the thought.*
*A burden you will carry for the rest of your days, but fortunately you will not have to carry it alone.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Goes to RomanceFates (not the Dark Urge one, but the one with an origin companion, whoever that may be)

Text.Value: I will honour Karlach's memory for the rest of my days. She should have died in battle not by my hand.
I will honour Wyll's memory, for the rest of my days.
I will eradicate the cult of Bhaal. One cultist at a time.
*Bittersweet it is to remember the life of one ended by your hand. But you are not that person anymore.*
*Gale. His death weighs upon you still.*
There's so much of this world I haven't seen - I will see it all. Starting now!
*You slept like a babe, straight through the night. Dreamless, thoughtless, and almost entirely free.*
I want to find a family of my own. A real one.
*Now your future is your own, so live it wisely, live it well - to your own nature be true.*
*But be careful lest you pen a tragic sequel to your tale.*
*Bhaal may have been your beginning, but he will not be your end.*
I will honour Lae'zel's memory, for the rest of my days.
*Lae'zel. Her death weighs upon you still.*
I will atone for my sins against the Baldurians by rebuilding their city.
*Though you are not governed by your Father anymore, your blood bears his taint. If you were to have sires of your own, they would be born Bhaalspawn.*
*But what will you do, now that your life is your own?*
*For the first time, you feel alone. Calm, you breathe.*
*Astarion. His death weighs upon you still.*
*And once you have, the world will be yours, not to conquer, but to explore.*
*Wyll. His death weighs upon you still.*
*Quil, the dreaming Bard. Her death weighs upon you still.*
*Somewhere, on the wind, you almost feel you hear a rumbling laugh.*
*Shadowheart. Her death weighs upon you still.*
There's so much of this world I haven't seen - damn the stares I'll get - I will see it all!

Synopsis: Custom ending for Cured Dark Urge
